\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 6 Meyer lemons (1 1/2 pounds)\uc0\u8232 4 cups sugar\u8232 4 cups water\
Cut each lemon in quarters, remove as many seeds as possible, and reserve the seeds.\'a0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade2.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade2.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 Slice the quartered lemons very thinly, removing and reserving any further seeds that appear, and add to a large nonreactive pot, like a dutch oven.\'a0 Add any juice from the cutting board.\'a0  \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade3.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade3.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 Cover the pot and let stand for 24 hours at room temperature.\'a0 \
After 24 hours, put the pot on the stove and bring the mixture to a boil over moderate heat. Once it boils, reduce the heat to a simmer and let the mixture reduce down for 45 minutes to an hour.\'a0  It should reduce down to 4 cups.\'a0  \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade4.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade4.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 Meanwhile, fill a large stock pot with water and bring that to a boil.\'a0 Wash the mason jars in hot, hot, soapy water, then rinse well.\'a0 Add jars to the boiling water  and boil for 15 minutes.\'a0 Then, turn off the heat and add the lids and let stand for ten minutes, or until the marmalade is ready.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade5.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade5.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs38 \cf3 Once the lemon-water mixture has done its reducing, the sugar goes in with constant stirring, and everything cooks for another 15-20 minutes, or until a teaspoon of mixture dropped onto a cold plate gels.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade6.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade6.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 Using tongs, remove the jars from the hot water and place on the counter.\'a0 Do not dry them, just go straight to ladling the marmalade.  Fill it to within 1/4 inch of the top.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://thepauperedchef.com/images/2008/02/meyerlemonmarmalade7.jpg"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1\fs24 \cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic meyerlemonmarmalade7.jpg \width10000 \height7500
}¬}}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural

\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa480\ql\qnatural

\fs38 \cf3 When you\'92re done, wipe the rims with a paper towel dipped into that boiled water, put the round sealing part on top of the jar, then screw on the caps.\
Transfer the jars back into the hot water bath and make sure they\'92re covered by at least an inch of water.\'a0 Boil vigorously  for at least 5 minutes, then transfer the jars out of the hot water onto a cooling rack.\
Allow to cool completely.\'a0 Make sure the tops of the jars don\'92t pop up and down, which would indicate that the seal didn't work. Marmalade should keep for up to a year.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl380\sa400\ql\qnatural
